   "source": [
    "# Goals of this Training\n",
    "   \n",
    "* Use Python to combine powerful libraries\n",
    "  - Numerical: Pandas, NumPy\n",
    "  - Scikit-Learn\n",
    "  - Image Manipulation\n",
    "* Know what you are doing\n",
    "* Appreciate the beauty of the language\n",
    "* Jupyter Notebooks are also very cool\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Exercise\n",
    "* Load spectral image from a matlab file (.mat) into a 3-dimensional matrix. (See `scipy.io.loadmat`)\n",
    "* Use the K-Means algorithm to find clusters in the image. (See `sklearn.cluster.KMeans`)\n",
    "* Do something with that information. E.g. create a picture where the spectral pixels are converted to a RGB image of the same (x,y) dimension."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Links\n",
    "* [XKCD color survey](https://blog.xkcd.com/2010/05/03/color-survey-results/)\n",
    "* Basics\n",
    " - [Python Imaging Library](https://python-pillow.org/)\n",
    " - [NumPy](https://numpy.org/)\n",
    " - [SciPy](https://www.scipy.org/)\n",
    " - [Pandas](https://pandas.pydata.org/)\n",
    " - [Matplotlib](https://matplotlib.org/)\n",
    " - [Jupyter Notebook](https://jupyter.org/)\n",
    "* Documentation and Tutorials\n",
    " - Python\n",
    "   + [Corey Schafer's Youtube Channel](https://www.youtube.com/user/schafer5/)\n",
    "   + [Python Documentation](https://docs.python.org/3/)\n",
    " - Numpy and all that\n",
    "   + [Keith Galli's Youtube Channel](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCq6XkhO5SZ66N04IcPbqNcw/featured)\n",
    "     - [Numpy Arrays](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GB9ByFAIAH4). Watch out for \"*boolean masking and advanced indexing*\" \n",
    "  at around 50'.\n",
    "   + [Numpy and SciPy offical Documentation](https://docs.scipy.org/doc/)\n",
    "   + [Machine Learning, Sci-Kit Learn](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GB9ByFAIAH4)\n",
    "* [Spyder vs. PyCharm](https://idlecoding.com/ide-comparison-spyder-vs-pycharm/). Spyder tries really hard to make global variables even more global, by retaining them in a context that it reuses between program invocations. The cited comparison is really comprehensive, but still nobody seems to have a problem with that misfeature."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Walkthrough: Reduce Image to Eight Colors\n",
    "A related but more obvious problem is: given an RGB image, reduce colors to, say, eight.\n",
    "\n",
    "* Load PNG image into NumPy array\n",
    "* Make sense of it\n",
    "* Use K-Means to find eight clusters\n",
    "* Reduce colors by assigning center's RGB to members\n",
    "* Convert NumPy array back into PNG"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "IMGFILE = 'veggie.png'"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Load Image from File: PIL\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Rant\n",
    "* PIL was the original Python Imaging Library\n",
    "* For some reason a fork was created\n",
    "* [Pillow](https://python-pillow.org/)\n",
    "* Takes a while to learn to interpret Google search hits in this way\n",
    "* Welcome to Open Source"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import PIL.Image\n",
    "\n",
    "img = PIL.Image.open(IMGFILE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": false,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },

     },
     "execution_count": 3,

    }
   ],

    "img"

  {

   "source": [

   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy\n",
    "imgarray = numpy.array(img)"

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Preparation before Clustering\n",
    "* Cut off Alpha plane\n",
    "* Clustering input: only \"3d\" RGB values"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "rgb = imgarray[:,:,0:3]\n",
    "alpha = imgarray[:,:,3]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(477, 686, 3)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 11,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "rgb.shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# remember for later\n",
    "nrows, ncols, _ = rgb.shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(477, 686)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 13,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "alpha.shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "While we have compatible x,y sizes, we are missing one dimension in the alpha matrix. We need this to stack alpha on top of the reduced image once we have it."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "alpha = alpha.reshape(alpha.shape + (1,))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This could have been done easier by slicing a *range* of size 1 instead ..."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "alpha = imgarray[:,:,3:]"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

    }

   "source": [
    "alpha.shape"

   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"

   },
   "source": [
    "### Excursion: matplotlib\n",
    "Completely irrelevant: see where the points are in the RGB colorspace. Could spend more time on it though; for example, the points could be colored."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": true
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {

     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {

   "source": [
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "\n",
    "from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = plt.figure()\n",
    "ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('R')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('G')\n",
    "ax.set_zlabel('B')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "rs = []\n",
    "gs = []\n",
    "bs = []\n",
    "for x, y in numpy.ndindex(nrows,ncols):\n",
    "    r,g,b = rgb[x,y]\n",
    "    rs.append(r)\n",
    "    gs.append(g)\n",
    "    bs.append(b)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"

   "source": [
    "ax.scatter(rs,gs,bs)\n",
    "fig"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Now Comes the Clustering\n",
    "\n",
    "* [scikit-learn](https://scikit-learn.org/)\n",
    "* Huge data science toolbox\n",
    "* [K-Means](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/generated/sklearn.cluster.KMeans.html): \"Given a set of data points, find N clusters and their centers\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We have a two-dimensional array of (r,g,b) values. KMeans is not interested in (x,y), so linearize the input.\n",
    "*Note* that reshaping an array is a zero-copy operation - it only gives a different view onto the same memory."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "rgb_linear = rgb.reshape(nrows*ncols, 3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Let KMeans find eight clusters ..."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "-"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "KMeans(algorithm='auto', copy_x=True, init='k-means++', max_iter=300,\n",
       "       n_clusters=8, n_init=10, n_jobs=None, precompute_distances='auto',\n",
       "       random_state=None, tol=0.0001, verbose=0)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 21,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.cluster import KMeans\n",
    "\n",
    "km = KMeans(n_clusters=8)\n",
    "km.fit(rgb_linear)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Use the result: output-properties\n",
    "* labels: cluster membership for each point in the input sequence\n",
    "* cluster_centers: eight RGB values"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "array([1, 1, 1, ..., 1, 1, 1], dtype=int32)"
      ]

     "execution_count": 22,

     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [

   ]

    "len(km.labels_)"
   ]

    {

    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "nrows*ncols"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "array([[ 67.20529747,  37.50360681,  61.3796182 ],\n",
       "       [254.94408609, 254.75471018, 254.53133237],\n",

      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 25,
     "metadata": {},

    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "km.cluster_centers_"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Clusters be their Centers\n",
    "Assign each point the RGB values of the center it is attached to"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "for idx, label in enumerate(km.labels_):\n",
    "    rgb_linear[idx] = km.cluster_centers_[label]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Post Processing: Restore Alpha, Back into RGBA\n",
    "*Note*: while we have manipulated the RGB cube via `rgb_linear` (a two-dimensional view of it), we use the original three-dimensional `rgb` array."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "imgarray = numpy.concatenate((rgb, alpha), axis=2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 28,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "reduced_img = PIL.Image.fromarray(imgarray, 'RGBA')"
   ]
  },
